  "notes": "Venetian. NE Italo-Romance language of Veneto, Trentino, Friuli, and Istria. ~3.8 million speakers. Reference: Veneziano. Straddles Gallo-Italic / Italo-Romance boundary. Key features: (1) 7-vowel system (Italo-Romance). (2) Interdental fricatives /θ, ð/ in some varieties. (3) Intervocalic lenition (Gallo-Italic-like). (4) Partial degemination. (5) No /y/ fronting. Former lingua franca of the eastern Mediterranean (Ferguson 2007, Zamboni 1974).",
